#use wml::debian::template title="Mailinglists concerning Debian events" BARETITLE=true

<p>There is a sizable number of mailing lists discussing events concerning
Debian. These are usually distinguished bu geographical location. The
following list is sorted from more specific to more generic - so you might
start reading from the top until you find an area which fits the event you
are thinking about.</p>

<ul>
  <li> <a href="mailto:debian-dug-by@lists.debian.org">Belarus</a>, please
  also mail to the <a
  href="mailto:debian-events-eu@lists.debian.org">european list</a>
  <li> <a href="mailto:debian-events-nl@lists.debian.org">Netherlands</a>
  <li> <a href="mailto:debian-events-eu@lists.debian.org">Europe (whether
  EU or not)</a>
  <li> <a href="mailto:debian-events-ha@lists.debian.org">Hispanic
  America</a>
  <li> <a href="mailto:debian-events-na@lists.debian.org">non-latin North
  America</a>
  <li> <a href="mailto:events@debian.org">everywhere else</a>, but we will
  probably coordinate using the <a
  href="mailto:debian-events-eu@lists.debian.org">european list</a>.
</ul>

<p>Just for reference - We would be delighted to see event-organizing
communities on other continents develop. If that happens do not hesitate to
mail to <a href="mailto:events@debian.org">the Events Team</a>. We will try
to help you.</p>
